mar <- par("mar")

2 Analysis

Reading in all the missing IDs

res <- mclapply(dir(".",pattern=".*-no-aln-IDs\\.txt"),scan,what="character",mc.cores=6L)
names(res) <- sub("-no-aln-IDs\\.txt","",dir(".",pattern=".*-no-aln-IDs\\.txt"))

2.1 Assess

Barplot them

barplot(elementLengths(res))

How do they overlap within one species?

Mostly the majority is absent in both

dev.null <- lapply(split(res,sub(".*-","",names(res))),function(ls){
  plot.new()
  grid.draw(venn.diagram(ls,
                         filename=NULL,
                         col=pal[1:2],
                         category.names=names(ls)))
})

2.2 Per species - intersection

Extract the absent sets

Potra01 <- intersect(res$`Potri03-Potra01`,res$`Potrs01-Potra01`)
Potri03 <- intersect(res$`Potra01-Potri03`,res$`Potrs01-Potri03`)
Potrs01 <- intersect(res$`Potra01-Potrs01`,res$`Potri03-Potrs01`)

Load the proteins

Potra01p <- readAAStringSet("/mnt/picea/storage/reference/Populus-tremula/v1.0/fasta/Potra01-protein-in-frame-representative.fa.gz")
Potri03p <- readAAStringSet("/mnt/picea/storage/reference/Populus-trichocarpa/v3.0/fasta/Ptrichocarpa_v3.0_210_peptide.fa.gz")
Potrs01p <- readAAStringSet("/mnt/picea/storage/reference/Populus-tremuloides/v1.0/fasta/Potrs01-protein-in-frame-representative.fa")

The vast majority of Potra and Potrs gene not aligning to other genomes is non-coding!

pander(table(Potra01 %in% sub("\\..*","",names(Potra01p))))
FALSE TRUE
393 40 
pander(table(Potrs01 %in% sub("\\..*","",names(Potrs01p))))
FALSE TRUE
373 12

export only the coding ones

write(Potra01[Potra01 %in% sub("\\..*","",names(Potra01p))],file="Potra01-never-aln-IDs.txt")
write(Potrs01[Potrs01 %in% sub("\\..*","",names(Potrs01p))],file="Potrs01-never-aln-IDs.txt")

and all of them for Potri

write(Potri03,file="Potri03-never-aln-IDs.txt")

Check for the union

Potra01 <- union(res$`Potri03-Potra01`,res$`Potrs01-Potra01`)
Potrs01 <- union(res$`Potra01-Potrs01`,res$`Potri03-Potrs01`)
Potri03 <- union(res$`Potra01-Potri03`,res$`Potrs01-Potri03`)

The majority of non aligning genes are pre-miRNA

Potra01 <- Potra01[grep("Potra",Potra01)]
Potrs01 <- Potrs01[grep("Potrs",Potrs01)]

There is no trend for Potri03 (not more on scaffold than on chrom.)

Potra01p <- readAAStringSet("/mnt/picea/storage/reference/Populus-tremula/v1.0/fasta/Potra01-protein.fa.gz")
Potra01p.state <- getProteinState(Potra01p)
Potrs01p <- readAAStringSet("/mnt/picea/storage/reference/Populus-tremuloides/v1.0/fasta/Potrs01-protein.fa.gz")
Potrs01p.state <- getProteinState(Potrs01p)
Potri03p.state <- getProteinState(Potri03p)

Most are coding in Potra01

pander(table(Potra01p.state[sub("\\..*","",names(Potra01p)) %in% Potra01]))
full-length 5p-partial fragment 3p-partial non-coding
202 14 33 16 25 
write(Potra01,file="Potra01-part-or-never-aln-IDs.txt")

Most are coding in Potrs01, but with an higher proportion of partials

pander(table(Potrs01p.state[sub("\\..*","",names(Potrs01p)) %in% Potrs01]))
full-length 5p-partial fragment 3p-partial non-coding
105 25 49 60 34 
write(Potrs01,file="Potrs01-part-or-never-aln-IDs.txt")

Check the status for Potri03p - they have some partial sequences, which are distributed accross chromosomes and scaffolds

pander(table(Potri03p.state))
full-length 5p-partial fragment 3p-partial non-coding
69874 710 117 2312 0 
pander(table(grepl("\\.T",names(Potri03p)[Potri03p.state != "full-length"])))
FALSE TRUE
2967 172

Check their sizes Most unaligned sequences are extremely short

plot.multidensity(list(Potra01=width(Potra01p),
                       Potrs01=width(Potrs01p),
                       Potri03=width(Potri03p),
                       Potra01.no.aln=width(Potra01p[sub("\\..*","",names(Potra01p)) %in% Potra01]),
                       Potrs01.no.aln=width(Potrs01p[sub("\\..*","",names(Potrs01p)) %in% Potrs01]),
                       Potri03.no.aln=width(Potri03p[sub("\\.[0-9]+\\|.*","",names(Potri03p)) %in% Potri03])
                       ),lwd=2,xlab="AA")
